rews' Collection of Poems, Songs and Lullabies''\n|{{Won}}\n|}\n\n===Emmy Award===\n<small>Note: The year given is the year of the ceremony</small>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Award\n!Performance\n!Result\n|-\n! colspan=4| Daytime Emmy Award\n|-\n|[[8th Daytime Emmy Awards|1981]]\n|[[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Performer in Children's Programming|Outstanding Individual Achievement in Children's Programming \u2013 Performers]]\n|''The CBS Festival of Lively Arts for Young People''\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n! colspan=4| Primetime Emmy Award\n|-\n|[[10th Primetime Emmy Awards|1958]]\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actress in a Limited Series or Movie|Actress \u2013 Best Single Performance \u2013 Lead or Support]]\n|''[[Cinderella (Rodgers and Hammerstein musical)|Cinderella]]''\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|[[17th Primetime Emmy Awards|1965]]\n|Outstanding Individual Achievements in Entertainment \u2013 Actors and Performers\n|''[[The Andy Williams Show]]''\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|[[24th Primetime Emmy Awards|1972]]\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Variety Special (Pre-Recorded)|Outstanding Single Program \u2013 Variety or Musical \u2013 Variety and Popular Music]]\n|''Julie and Carol at Lincoln Center''\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[25th Primetime Emmy Awards|1973]]\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding New Series|Outstanding New Series]]\n|rowspan=2|''[[The Julie Andrews Hour]]''\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Variety Series|Outstanding Variety Musical Series]]\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|[[47th Primetime Emmy Awards|1995]]\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Individual Performance in a Variety or Music Program|Outstanding Individual Performance in a Variety or Music Program]]\n|''The Sound of Julie Andrews''\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|[[56th Primetime Emmy Awards|2004]]\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Limited Series or Movie|Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Miniseries or a Movie]]\n|''[[Eloise at Christmastime]]''\n|{{