 Andrews Hour}}''\n| Host\n| \n|-\n| 1973\n| ''[[Julie on Sesame Street]]''\n| rowspan=6| Herself\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=3|1974\n| ''[[The Dick Cavett Show]]''\n|\n|-\n| ''Julie and Dick at Covent Garden''\n|\n|-\n| ''Julie and Jackie: How Sweet It Is''\n|\n|-\n| 1975\n| ''Julie: My Favorite Things''\n|\n|-\n| 1977\n| ''[[The Muppet Show]]''\n|\n|-\n| 1978\n| ''Julie Andrews: One Step Into Spring''\n| Herself&nbsp;\u2013 host\n|\n|-\n| 1981\n| ''The CBS Festival of Lively Arts for Young People''\n| rowspan=4| Herself\n| \n|-\n| 1987\n| ''Julie Andrews: The Sound of Christmas''\n|\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[[Julie & Carol: Together Again]]''\n|\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''Julie Andrews in Concert''\n|\n|-\n| 1991\n| ''[[Our Sons]]''\n| Audrey Grant\n| TV movie\n|-\n| rowspan=2|1992\n| ''[[Julie (TV series)|Julie]]''\n| Julie Carlisle\n| TV series (7 episodes)\n|-\n| ''[[The King and I (1992 studio cast album)|The King & I]]''\n| Anna\n| TV musical\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''Sound of Orchestra''\n| rowspan=2| Host\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=2|1995\n| ''The Sound of Julie Andrews''\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Victor/Victoria (1995 film)|Victor/Victoria]]''\n| Victoria Grant <br/> Count Victor Grezhinski\n| TV movie\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[One Special Night]]''\n| Catherine\n|\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[On Golden Pond (2001 film)|On Golden Pond]]''\n| Ethel Thayer\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2003\n| ''[[Eloise at the Plaza]]''\n| rowspan=2| Nanny\n| TV movie\n|-\n| ''[[Eloise at Christmastime]]''\n| TV movie\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''Broadway: The American Musical''\n| Narrator/Host\n| Six-part PBS documentary series about Musical Theatre\n|-\n| 2009\u201310 <br/> 2012\u201317\n| ''[[Great Performances]]''\n| Narrator/Host\n| Episode \"[[Vienna New Year's Concert|From Vienna: The New Year's Celebration]],\" \n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[The Colbert Report]]''\n| Guest\n| \n|-\n| 2014-17\n| ''[[The Graham Norton Show]]''\n| Guest\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Julie's Greenroom]]''\n| Miss Julie\n| Co-creator; [[Netflix]] series\n|-\n|2020\n|''[[Bridgerton (TV series)|Bridgerton]]''\n|Lady Whistledown\n|Voice; 8 episodes - [[Netflix]] series \n|}\n\n=== Stage ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1954\u201355\n| ''{{sortname|The|Boy Friend|The Boy Friend (musical)}}''\n| Polly Brown\n| \n|-\n| 1956\u201359\n| ''[[My Fair Lady]]''\n| [[Eliza Doolittle]]\n|\n|-\n| 1960\u201362\n| ''[[Camelot (musical)|Camelot]]''\n|  [[Guinevere|Queen Guinevere]]\n| \n|- Queen of Camelot and wife of [[King Arthur]]\n| 1993\n| ''[[Putting It Together]]''\n| Amy\n|\n|-\n| 1995\u201397\n| ''[[Victor/Victoria (musical)|Victor/Victoria]]''\n| Victoria Grant / Count Victor Grezhinski\n| \n|}\n\n== Accolades ==\n===Academy Awards===\n<small>Note: The year given is the year of the ceremony</small>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Award\n!Performance\n!Result\n|-\n||[[37th Academy Awards|1965]]\n|rowspan=3|[[Academy Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n|| ''[[Mary Poppins (film)|Mary Poppins]]''\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|[[38th Academy Awards|1966]]\n|''[[The Sound of Music (film)|The Sound of Music]]''\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|[[55th Academy Awards|1983]]\n|''[[Victor/Victoria]]''\n|{{Nom}}\n|}\n\n===Golden Globe Awards===\n<small>Note: The year given is the year of the ceremony</small>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Award\n!Performance\n!Result\n|-\n|[[22nd Golden Globe Awards|1965]]\n|rowspan=2|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Actress \u2013 Motion Picture Comedy or Musical|Best Actress \u2013 Motion Picture Comedy or Musical]]\n| ''[[Mary Poppins (film)|Mary Poppins]]''\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|[[23rd Golden Globe Awards|1966]]\n|''[[The Sound of Music (film)|The Sound of Music]]''\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|[[24th Golden Globe Awards|1967]]\n|[[Golden Globe Award#Retired awards|Henrietta Award \u2014 World Film Favorite \u2014 Female]]\n|  \u2014\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[25th Golden Globe Awards|1968]]\n|Best Actress \u2013 Motion Picture Comedy or Musical\n|''[[Thoroughly Modern Millie]]''\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|ro